FBIS4-60713 "drnes103_r_94004" FBIS-NES-94-103 Daily Report 25 May 1994 India ASEAN Asked To Help Develop `Global Trading System' ASEAN Asked To Help Develop `Global Trading System' BK2505091194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 25 May 94 BK2505091194 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] India has sought the cooperation of ASEAN -- the Association of South East Asian Nations -- for adopting a common strategy to evolve a nondiscriminatory global trading system. The commerce minister, Mr. Pranab Mukherjee, has said that the strategy will bridge the trade gap between the developing and the developed countries with the World Trade Organization coming into effect from January next.
